{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c03f682b-ba7f-475f-960d-fbedbde311e6",
    "name": "Small Dispute",
    "description": "Complete Postman guide for the Small Dispute feature.\n\nBase URL: {{base_url}}/small-dispute (adjust prefix to match your router mount path)\n\nVariables to set:\n- base_url: http://localhost:5001/api\n- token_a: JWT for Person A (Creator)\n- token_b: JWT for Person B (Joiner)\n- dispute_id: filled automatically from Step 1 response\n\nRun requests in order 1 → 5.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Create Room (Person A)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status is 2xx\", function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});",
              "",
              "let json = {};",
              "try { json = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
              "",
              "if (json.invite_code) pm.collectionVariables.set(\"invite_code\", json.invite_code);",
              "if (json.dispute_id) pm.collectionVariables.set(\"dispute_id\", json.dispute_id);",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"invite_code present\", () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"invite_code\"));",
              "pm.test(\"dispute_id present\", () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"dispute_id\"));"
            ],
            "id": "026d591d-e0ac-442d-9e8e-61317a819945"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "0edf7042-567a-4e60-a180-a2f119c97545",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token_a}}"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": ""
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/small-dispute/create",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "small-dispute",
            "create"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Person A creates a dispute room. No request body needed — auth token identifies the creator.\n\nExpected response:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Room created\",\n  \"invite_code\": \"A1B2C3\",\n  \"dispute_id\": \"64abc...\"\n}\n\nCopy invite_code and dispute_id into your collection variables before continuing."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Join Room (Person B)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status is 2xx\", function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});",
              "",
              "let json = {};",
              "try { json = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
              "",
              "if (json.dispute_id) pm.collectionVariables.set(\"dispute_id\", json.dispute_id);"
            ],
            "id": "b952beed-a1f7-4252-bc71-1dc728de4932"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "4372c8a1-4729-490a-a1c9-f3c946f8ef2d",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          },
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token_b}}"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"invite_code\": \"{{invite_code}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/small-dispute/join",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "small-dispute",
            "join"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Person B joins using the invite code from Step 1.\n\nExpected response:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Joined successfully\",\n  \"dispute_id\": \"64abc...\"\n}\n\nSocket event emitted to the room: 'user_joined'\n{\n  \"message\": \"Opponent has joined!\"\n}\n\nEdge cases:\n- Same user as creator → 400 'Cannot join your own room'\n- Wrong/expired code → 404 'Invalid code'"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Start Recording (Person A only)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status is 2xx\", function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});"
            ],
            "id": "7cef4b9d-a5a5-49b9-83c4-fa37ec44cbfa"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "a2b66a21-f478-4dab-903d-0521ebd003b5",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          },
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token_a}}"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"dispute_id\": \"{{dispute_id}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/small-dispute/start",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "small-dispute",
            "start"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Only the creator (Person A) can call this. Both users must be in the room first.\n\nExpected response:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Session started\",\n  \"status\": \"RECORDING\"\n}\n\nSocket event emitted to both users: 'timer_start'\n{\n  \"duration\": 30\n}\n\nBoth users now have 30 seconds to record their audio argument.\n\nEdge cases:\n- Person B calls this → 403 'Only Creator can start'\n- Joiner not present yet → 400 'Wait for opponent'"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "4a. Submit Audio — Person A",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status is 2xx\", function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});"
            ],
            "id": "e86ea6a5-9f1a-43cf-9aba-dd156d55c2e5"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "76c53b3c-a15f-4a65-8951-a9b1e7027f08",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token_a}}"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "formdata",
          "formdata": [
            {
              "key": "dispute_id",
              "value": "{{dispute_id}}",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "key": "audio",
              "description": "Select any .mp3 or .webm audio file from your machine",
              "type": "file",
              "src": "/path/to/your/audio_a.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/small-dispute/submit",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "small-dispute",
            "submit"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Person A submits their recorded audio argument.\n\nIMPORTANT: This is multipart/form-data NOT JSON. Set the body to form-data with:\n- dispute_id (text field)\n- audio (file field — attach an actual audio file)\n\nExpected response if Person B hasn't submitted yet:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Waiting for opponent\"\n}\n\nSocket event emitted: 'status_update'\n{\n  \"message\": \"One user submitted.\"\n}"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "4b. Submit Audio — Person B (Triggers Verdict)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status is 2xx\", function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});"
            ],
            "id": "2268d7e3-ab63-4069-91cb-226230087bea"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "085b8fa1-115f-4f79-8135-517bda8342b5",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token_b}}"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "formdata",
          "formdata": [
            {
              "key": "dispute_id",
              "value": "{{dispute_id}}",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "key": "audio",
              "description": "Select any .mp3 or .webm audio file from your machine",
              "type": "file",
              "src": "/path/to/your/audio_b.mp3"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/small-dispute/submit",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "small-dispute",
            "submit"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Person B submits their audio. Since both audios are now present, this triggers the AI Judge.\n\nWhat happens internally:\n1. Both audio files are read and sent to Gemini as inline base64\n2. AI returns a verdict JSON\n3. Dispute status set to COMPLETED\n4. Verdict saved to dispute.result\n\nExpected HTTP response:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Verdict broadcasted\"\n}\n\nSocket events emitted in sequence:\n\n'processing_start'\n{\n  \"message\": \"Judge is analyzing...\"\n}\n\n'verdict_ready'\n{\n  \"status\": \"COMPLETED\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"verdict\": \"The Creator is correct because...\",\n    \"conclusion\": \"A neutral summary.\",\n    \"logic_score\": { \"creator\": 85, \"joiner\": 60 },\n    \"emotional_intelligence\": { \"creator\": 40, \"joiner\": 90 },\n    \"fact_accuracy\": { \"creator\": 80, \"joiner\": 50 }\n  }\n}\n\nNote: The verdict is delivered via socket. The HTTP response just confirms it was triggered."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Get Dispute Details",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status is 2xx\", function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});"
            ],
            "id": "7ece8dcf-fd88-487f-8a34-2f35b9add0e2"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "c898bc07-d5e1-4cbd-8f97-1210e56660f3",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token_a}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/small-dispute/{{dispute_id}}",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "small-dispute",
            "{{dispute_id}}"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Fetch full dispute details at any point in the flow. Useful for:\n- Loading screen while waiting for opponent\n- Checking current status\n- Reading the final result after COMPLETED\n\nExpected response (after COMPLETED):\n{\n  \"_id\": \"64abc...\",\n  \"creator_id\": { \"_id\": \"...\", \"firstName\": \"John\", ... },\n  \"joiner_id\": { \"_id\": \"...\", \"firstName\": \"Jane\", ... },\n  \"invite_code\": \"A1B2C3\",\n  \"status\": \"COMPLETED\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"verdict\": \"...\",\n    \"conclusion\": \"...\",\n    \"logic_score\": { \"creator\": 85, \"joiner\": 60 },\n    \"emotional_intelligence\": { \"creator\": 40, \"joiner\": 90 },\n    \"fact_accuracy\": { \"creator\": 80, \"joiner\": 50 }\n  }\n}"
      },
      "response": []
    }
  ],
